1959;;The Heart of a Man;;British;;Herbert Wilcox;;Frankie Vaughan, Anne Heywood;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Heart_of_a_Man;;Sailor Frankie Martin is offered a thousand pounds by an eccentric tramp if he can earn a hundred pounds in a week by honest means. Frankie tries his hand as a boxer, a bouncer and a commissionaire, and finally finds success as a singer. He also falls for the charms of night club chanteuse Julie, and this leads to further success when he wins a recording contract.